and Zuma Beach\n\n\u00be Project Description:\n\n  This project was identified in the 2015 PCH Safety Study and includes installing new raised medians and improvements.  New raised medians are proposed east and west of PCH and Paradise Cove Road.  The proposed improvements also include the relocation of the existing bus stop and new signage.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 6364, "end_char_idx": 6840, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "789d7632-9032-4f10-966b-4fc10d73ad5a": {"__data__": {"id_": "789d7632-9032-4f10-966b-4fc10d73ad5a", "embedding": null, "metadata": {}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "160e5c6e-8113-4cdf-b20c-d991fc84f6a4", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {}, "hash": "85048d5fc764069bdb5106e18c9cb792b33a75375e06a94daf4cbf884a2a5c0d", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "7565fb65-b37f-4cf1-b95a-674204c480d4", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "590c0467c48ca6ea9b613a76d49b64598f437d678f122eeeaa551cf0a19101d8", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "d2b0febb-139d-4f4f-9be0-11400493edb7", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "f61ef20d4ce19befe4b8dd2220541b4fd380033b4194aa8faeaf78ae80393d12", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "The project will also include the installation of new raised medians on PCH in the areas where the double yellow lines exist in the vicinity of Zuma Beach, specifically where the yellow paddles are installed.\n\n\u00be Project Updates: City has submitted an application through Measure R and is waiting for the agreement.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 6844, "end_char_idx": 7158, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "d2b0febb-139d-4f4f-9be0-11400493edb7": {"__data__": {"id_": "d2b0febb-139d-4f4f-9be0-11400493edb7", "embedding": null, "metadata": {}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "160e5c6e-8113-4cdf-b20c-d991fc84f6a4", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {}, "hash": "85048d5fc764069bdb5106e18c9cb792b33a75375e06a94daf4cbf884a2a5c0d", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "789d7632-9032-4f10-966b-4fc10d73ad5a", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "d4cca02ea04d8a671d01a73206b962011e0e5ae4141de573ed21d2647040e2d1", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "4723d51e-5583-44d2-b20b-d64db113180f", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "f8421b609c9a028f736d77ceaa953191bcc2bf63c853291f7e17f93d37e7edfe", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "PCH Crosswalk Improvements at Big Rock Drive and 20326 PCH\n\n\u00be Project Description:\n\n This project was identified in the 2015 PCH Safety Study and includes the installation of overhead warning signs and raised medians on PCH. New flashing warning beacons will be installed approximately 200 feet east and west of 20326 PCH (Moonshadow\u2019s Restaurant). New raised medians, along with a pedestrian refuge area, are planned for this area.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 7160, "end_char_idx": 7592, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "4723d51e-5583-44d2-b20b-d64db113180f": {"__data__": {"id_": "4723d51e-5583-44d2-b20b-d64db113180f", "embedding": null, "metadata": {}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "160e5c6e-8113-4cdf-b20c-d991fc84f6a4", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {}, "hash": "85048d5fc764069bdb5106e18c9cb792b33a75375e06a94daf4cbf884a2a5c0d", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "d2b0febb-139d-4f4f-9be0-11400493edb7", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "f61ef20d4ce19befe4b8dd2220541b4fd380033b4194aa8faeaf78ae80393d12", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "21b1bae0-38c0-4c08-940c-2cd192978412", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "dad1e64a8c230c7a740e9bff8fc29a248f1c57efbdc7d50500ef902aba257869", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "A new overhead flashing \u201csignal ahead\u201d beacon will be installed 400 feet east of PCH and Big Rock Drive intersection.\n\nKanan Dume Biofilter\n\n\u00be Project  Description:\n\n    This  project  was  identified  in  the  City\u2019s  Enhanced Watershed Management Plan (EWMP). This project includes the installation of  a  biofilter  on  Kanan  Dume  Drive  to  capture  and  treat  stormwater.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 7593, "end_char_idx": 7972, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "21b1bae0-38c0-4c08-940c-2cd192978412": {"__data__": {"id_": "21b1bae0-38c0-4c08-940c-2cd192978412", "embedding": null, "metadata": {}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "160e5c6e-8113-4cdf-b20c-d991fc84f6a4", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {}, "hash": "85048d5fc764069bdb5106e18c9cb792b33a75375e06a94daf4cbf884a2a5c0d", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "4723d51e-5583-44d2-b20b-d64db113180f", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "f8421b609c9a028f736d77ceaa953191bcc2bf63c853291f7e17f93d37e7edfe", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "c0b6ccea-1215-4da1-8c05-86dc0ba5b425", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "69f904be4243fa6143fc86aff49defa90baed4931d7dfbe38e53757ec70c2190", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "The project  is  intended  to  assist  with  Municipal  Separate  Storm  Sewer  System (MS4) Discharge Permit requirements.Page 5 of 6\n\n\nAgenda Item # 4.B.\n\nCity Traffic Signals Backup Power\n\n\u00be Project  Description:\n\n    This  project  will  include  upgrading  the  backup  power system to the City\u2019s traffic signals on Civic Center Way, Webb Way, Malibu Canyon Road,", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 7974, "end_char_idx": 8342, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "c0b6ccea-1215-4da1-8c05-86dc0ba5b425": {"__data__": {"id_": "c0b6ccea-1215-4da1-8c05-86dc0ba5b425", "embedding": null, "metadata": {}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "160e5c6e-8113-4cdf-b20c-d991fc84f6a4", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {}, "hash": "85048d5fc764069bdb5106e18c9cb792b33a75375e06a94daf4cbf884a2a5c0d", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "21b1bae0-38c0-4c08-940c-2cd192978412", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "dad1e64a8c230c7a740e9bff8fc29a248f1c57efbdc7d50500ef902aba257869", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "df786ac2-b3a9-43fb-9f61-4973ea965068", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "3e74766ad88ac4b73e535734cb5fda1dbbc73e22bccd559544ba397a0cc17acc", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "and Winter Canyon Road \u00be Updates: Project is in the preliminary design phase\n\n\u00be Project  Schedule:\n\n  Preliminary  design  will  determine  if  signals  need  to  be upgraded\nStaff has also  prepared a Public Works  Quarterly Update flier.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 8343, "end_char_idx": 8582, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "df786ac2-b3a9-43fb-9f61-4973ea965068": {"__data__": {"id_": "df786ac2-b3a9-43fb-9f61-4973ea965068", "embedding": null, "metadata": {}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "160e5c6e-8113-4cdf-b20c-d991fc84f6a4", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {}, "hash": "85048d5fc764069bdb5106e18c9cb792b33a75375e06a94daf4cbf884a2a5c0d", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "c0b6ccea-1215-4da1-8c05-86dc0ba5b425", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "69f904be4243fa6143fc86aff49defa90baed4931d7dfbe38e53757ec70c2190", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "a7a39294-c71e-40e9-9cf4-20b2d71b63dc", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "36db0eb42449a41e4ba6a19079e07c837592128f6d275e795636fe6c3565665f", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "This flier will include  a variety  of  Public  Works  statistics,  including  Projects  Under  Design,  Citizen  Request, Encroachment Permits Issued, and the amount of Development Reviews performed.\n\n  The flier  will  also  include  a  \u201cProject  Spotlight\u201d  that  will  describe  a  City  capital  improvement project.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 8584, "end_char_idx": 8905, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "a7a39294-c71e-40e9-9cf4-20b2d71b63dc": {"__data__": {"id_": "a7a39294-c71e-40e9-9cf4-20b2d71b63dc", "embedding": null, "metadata": {}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "160e5c6e-8113-4cdf-b20c-d991fc84f6a4", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {}, "hash": "85048d5fc764069bdb5106e18c9cb792b33a75375e06a94daf4cbf884a2a5c0d", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "df786ac2-b3a9-43fb-9f61-4973ea965068", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "3e74766ad88ac4b73e535734cb5fda1dbbc73e22bccd559544ba397a0cc17acc", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "The Quarterly Update Flier will be brought to the Public Works Commission every quarter and then posted on the City\u2019s website.ATTACHMENT: Quarter 2 \u2013 Public Works CIP Update Flyer\nPage 6 of 6\nAgenda Item # 4.B.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 8907, "end_char_idx": 9117, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}}, "docstore/metadata": {"ec11de64-f697-430f-8101-fffe20a2dbe4": {"doc_hash": "6a2f932105df8f4ddb67df384a9e3ab827ee8e4906f00ae420828d12c1c3f98e", "ref_doc_id": "160e5c6e-8113-4cdf-b20c-d991fc84f6a4"}, "1efaf51a-2fe9-43a8-a444-61c13d606aff": {"doc_hash": "ad2ac5787b2369933fbe12cc971f68f3eae31cb8b2f2821d9b5712d29172cc08", "ref_doc_id": "160e5c6e-8113-4cdf-b20c-d991fc84f6a4"}, "e7421782-cff3-4355-a727-f3610bb15af1": {"doc_hash": "15d278ed28c3eab972b88b92b20bd4a90a3741378b13bd2868e93fad851b151a", "ref_doc_id": "160e5c6e-8113-4cdf-b20c-d991fc84f6a4"}, "7c40ef3d-3271-4cb5-a9a0-77be72a3538c": {"doc_hash": "b69cf3b0e81b33df006b68248585505e0f0d80a289ae13df418851c5430f7ad3", "ref_doc_id": "160e5c6e-8113-4cdf-b20c-d991fc84f6a4"}, "8a7a0334-19db-42ba-b80e-ed77f7ed7dd8": {"doc_hash": "4de93bc3ad912b8d6d88f05c13eeead5d16dbf496458f33fdf6234f7b0fdcfc2", "ref_doc_id": "160e5c6e-8113-4cdf-b20c-d991fc84f6a4"}, "f4bd2e09-d645-4f7a-846f-3dc6a662728f": {"doc_hash": "837f4ff906d2d16c7da94339b80c1e3611211dc26120f048f8d902945ee2a9df", "ref_doc_id": "160e5c6e-8113-4cdf-b20c-d991fc84f6a4"}, "f9db1e45-15dc-4a4c-9a79-6eb4d0c95d71": {"doc_hash": "0de325c8bd9baa4f78f5d8abfc9e4b8eb4aa28a8b3a39d1d39638f965f8a8f32", "ref_doc_id": "160e5c6e-8113-4cdf-b20c-d991fc84f6a4"}, "8a5b8c09-c125-4361-9652-c5c789e8ced7": {"doc_hash": "16d7a1749810f4ce7466f11c94e1d989e72e425d9e75c3f776ad39cf7dc5ae74", "ref_doc_id": "160e5c6e-8113-4cdf-b20c-d991fc84f6a4"}, "2b9f156f-9582-4952-8fa6-1f118c6c1648": {"doc_hash": "16d6340762ed93dfe0178594dfe97d890fe0485849d86473185ac539239b7a16", "ref_doc_id": "160e5c6e-8113-4cdf-b20c-d99